like a fire ant. Louisiana's crawfish season normally peaks in
February, with plenty of fat, juicy mudbugs going from fishermen's
nets into propane-fired boiling pots. But crawfish farmers, fish
mongers and restaurant owners agree: This the worst season in
memory. (Koingsmark, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
