</P>
<P>
   The firings were necessary, said  &UR; Nancy Nielsen &LR;  of the Times.
``This is not a First Amendment issue. There is no First Amendment
right to transmit pornography over the company's e-mail system, or
to view pornography in the workplace.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SHOPPING OPPORTUNITIES &LR;
</P>
<P>
   - Dining in a restaurant in St. Petersburg recently,  &UR; Gladys &LR; 
and  &UR; Simon Palmer &LR;  were handed a Russian shopping brochure inviting
``Dear Sir'' to ``stop by our shop, browse through our extensive
catalogs and choose a woman to suit your tastes.''
</P>
<P>
   The catalog attached includes color photos of 19 women, and data
on each one's age (from 19 to 45), height (5-foot-2 to 5-foot-8)
and weight (105 to 150). Accompanying prose promises a woman who
``will not be scarred by hardship. She will accept you as you are.
Do you want to find someone responsive and interesting, a friend
and caring mother for your children, wonderful woman and wife? Take
the first step forward.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Opening and shutting its jaws, something all morays do to pump
water over their gills, it is the scariest-looking thing I've seen
outside of a Grateful Dead concert.''
</P>
<P>
   -  &UR; Bruce Watson  &LR; in a Smithsonian magazine story about the
wonders of eels.
</P>
