of his great-grandfather's fight with a grizzly bear when American
Indians claimed the San Fernando Valley as their own. It is a story
passed down through the generations, a lingering reminder of a
tribe that Ortega said numbered in the thousands and now counts
only some 300 people in the Valley. By Troy Anderson. (Will move in
the ``n'' California news file.)
