A8440 &Cx1f; tad-z
u e BC-MITCHELL-PBS07-COX     02-06 0177
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MITCHELL-PBS07-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Former CNN chief becomes first woman to head PBS
 &HT;    By Phil Kloer
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Pat Mitchell has been named the first female
president of PBS. Mitchell, formerly president of CNN Productions
and a native of Statesboro, Ga., will be officially announced as
PBS president today at the National Press Club. The PBS Board of
Directors voted to appoint Mitchell in a closed-door session Friday
afternoon in Miami.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's the third act I've dreamed of,'' said Mitchell, 57. ``I'm
excited and enthusiastic, and I know I have the passion,'' she said
Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
   Mitchell said she informed Ted Turner she might become president
of PBS last Monday. ``He was terrific. He was very supportive and
gave me a high five.''
</P>
<P>
   Mitchell will succeed Ervin Duggan, who resigned in October. She
met with the PBS board in Miami on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   ``Atlanta's going to stay home. I'll be commuting for a while,''
she said.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
