<P>
   ``Al Gore takes the stage in his buns-of-steel blue jeans, and
the crowd gasps. ABC's Ted Koppel will later call the jeans
`particularly snug,' but that does not begin to describe them. How
tight are they? Let's just say that nobody in the crowd of young
voters will ever have to ask the vice president whether he wears
boxers or briefs.'' (Roger Simon, US News and World Report) &QL; 
