formally as the annual World Memory Championships. The contest
produced a U.S. winner, Tatiana Cooley, 28, who will fly to London
to compete against some of the world's most steel-trap minds in
tasks such as memorizing the order of a deck of cards in 60 seconds
and tagging hundreds of words, faces, numbers and playing cards,
storing them in mental file cabinets and retrieving them in
seconds. (Edward Keating/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
